column1: #Text=Tenterfield is a town in the New England region of the Australian state of New South Wales .
#Text=Commercial airlines fly to larger rural centres around Tenterfield .
#Text=Most airports , such as Armidale , Casino , Lismore , Toowoomba and Ballina , are between 2 and 3 hours away .
#Text=Car rentals are available at all regional airports within a few hours of Tenterfield .
#Text=The only way to access Tenterfield is by road .
#Text=The New England Highway , which extends from Maitland , New South Wales , to Toowoomba in southern Queensland , is the major highway which passes through Tenterfield .
#Text=This is the main alternative to the Pacific Highway between Sydney and Brisbane .
#Text=The Bruxner Highway , travelling east/west , connects Tenterfield with Ballina , Lismore and Casino in the east and Texas and Goondiwindi in the west .
#Text=A National Trust building that contains a significant collection of Sir Edward Parkes relics .
#Text=The Tenterfield Saddlery was classified by the National Trust of Australia in 1972 .
#Text=Peter Allen , singer and songwriter , has perpetuated the memory of George Woolnough in one of his best known songs " The Tenterfield Saddler " .
#Text=Tenterfield has cafes , pizza shops , bakeries , burger shops and restaurants .
#Text=Being on a main highway between Sydney and Brisbane most food options are on the main street .
#Text=Saddler 's Cafe - +61 2 6736 4400 - 212 Rouse St - Good quality modern Australian food .
#Text=Tenterfield Bowling Club - +61 2 6736 1023 - 83 Molesworth St. Typical club food including " Hot Rock "
#Text=Lounge Bar with log fire in winter Main from $ 14.50 .
#Text=Free Austar with 3 sport and movie channels .
#Text=+61 2 6736 1023 - One of the only accommodation options in town and off the highway .
#Text=Truck and car noise can be annoying at highway motels .
#Text=Has pay as you go Wi-Fi in most rooms .
#Text=Fairways Lodge ( Tenterfield Golf Club ) +61 2 6736 1480 - Also off the highway .
#Text=IT is about 2-3 km out of the town centre .
#Text=Settlers Motor Inn , New England Highway ; Undercover parking , swimming pool with spa , close to shopping centre , heating & air conditioning , 02 6736 2333
#Text=Bald Rock is the largest exposed granite type rock in Australia and the main feature of this park .
#Text=This rock is 750 m long and 500 m wide , rising 200 m above the surrounding forest .
#Text=Bluff Rock situated 10 km south of Tenterfield on the New England Highway .
